# Git workflow (FlowOS)

**`main` = production.** Never push or merge to `main` without the founder's explicit approval.

## Start work

- **Runbook session:** new branch from updated `main` — `m2/session-N-short-name` (e.g. `m2/session-2-routing`).
- **UI/UX tweak:** `tweak/short-description` from `main`.
- **Docs only:** `docs/short-description`.

```powershell
git checkout main && git pull origin main
git checkout -b m2/session-N-short-name
```

## While working

- Commit on the branch (multiple commits per session OK).
- Push branch to `origin` for backup — **not** `main`.
- Before merge ask: `npm run build` && `npm run lint` pass locally.

## End of session — required agent behavior

Report: branch, commits, build/lint, which **merge bundle** (B1–B5, see `docs/foundation/governance/GIT_WORKFLOW.md`).

**Ask:** "Merge to `main`? (requires your approval)"

If bundle complete (e.g. B4 = sessions 4+5): emphasize bundle ready, still wait for yes.

**Never** `git push origin main`, **never** merge to `main`, **never** assume approval.

## After founder approves merge

```powershell
git checkout main && git pull origin main
git merge <branch> --no-ff
npm run build && npm run lint
git push origin main
```

Verify production URL; append [july-log.md](docs/execution/logs/july-log.md).

